A

acceptsJob(Job) - Method in class facility.Robot
Checks if a robot accepts a job
To do that, the robot calculate preemptively the paths needed to perform a job and stores them in memory if it is accepted
If a robot accepted a job, and the method takesJob() is called, a robot will take the last accepted job, stored in memory
Everytime this method is called, any previously calculated paths that weren't taken will be cleared and lost
